[ENTHRALLING INSTRUMENTAL
MUSIC PLAYING]

1208
01:00:14,820 --> 01:00:15,696
[GROANS]

1209
01:00:15,780 --> 01:00:17,615
[NECK CRACKING] Who's next then?

1210
01:00:17,698 --> 01:00:19,033
- [YELLS]
- [BOTH SHRIEK]

1211
01:00:19,116 --> 01:00:21,118
Otto, a security guard
has the truck keys!

1212
01:00:21,202 --> 01:00:23,454
Crazy eyes?
Tragic sense of fashion?

1213
01:00:23,537 --> 01:00:24,622
Yeah. How did you know?

1214
01:00:24,705 --> 01:00:25,831
Marge Malone.

1215
01:00:26,582 --> 01:00:28,876
<i>-Ethel!
- Otto!</i>

1216
01:00:28,959 --> 01:00:30,836
She's not just my nemesis,

1217
01:00:30,920 --> 01:00:32,963
she's also my enemy.

1218
01:00:33,047 --> 01:00:34,298
Love to hear about it,
but right now,

1219
01:00:34,381 --> 01:00:36,008
- what do we do?
- Get those keys.

1220
01:00:36,091 --> 01:00:38,135
I'll create a distraction
so you can get out of there.

1221
01:00:39,678 --> 01:00:41,806
- Come here, you!
- [GASPING]

1222
01:00:45,893 --> 01:00:46,936
[ODIE WHIMPERS]

1223
01:00:50,564 --> 01:00:52,525
Did you see that?
That's indoor cat style!

1224
01:00:52,608 --> 01:00:53,859
[GRUNTS]

1225
01:00:55,861 --> 01:00:57,196
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

1226
01:00:58,364 --> 01:00:59,782
[SHRIEKS]

1227
01:00:59,865 --> 01:01:01,033
[GRUNTS]

1228
01:01:02,076 --> 01:01:03,118
MARGE: No, no, no.

1229
01:01:03,202 --> 01:01:05,412
You're not getting away.
I've already called the pound.

1230
01:01:05,496 --> 01:01:07,873
Your days of thievery end today.

1231
01:01:07,957 --> 01:01:08,833
[BUZZER SOUNDING]

1232
01:01:08,916 --> 01:01:11,293
WOMAN OVER PA:
<i>Attempted perimeter breach.</i>

1233
01:01:12,378 --> 01:01:14,630
<i>Attempted perimeter breach.</i>

1234
01:01:14,713 --> 01:01:17,341
<i>Attempted perimeter breach.</i>

1235
01:01:17,424 --> 01:01:18,634
Otto.

1236
01:01:18,717 --> 01:01:23,180
<i>Attempted perimeter breach.
Attempted perimeter breach.</i>

1237
01:01:24,139 --> 01:01:27,977
- Junior, sorry about this.
- Sorry? For what?

1238
01:01:28,060 --> 01:01:30,020
[ALL GRUNT]

1239
01:01:30,563 --> 01:01:31,981
[GRUNTS]

1240
01:01:32,064 --> 01:01:33,065
Vic?

1241
01:01:40,990 --> 01:01:42,658
What are you doing?

1242
01:01:45,327 --> 01:01:47,788
Vic! Don't you go.

1243
01:01:47,872 --> 01:01:49,039
Vic!

1244
01:01:50,541 --> 01:01:51,834
Please!

1245
01:01:57,006 --> 01:01:57,882
Send security

1246
01:01:57,965 --> 01:01:59,508
- to the loading dock.
- [STATIC BUZZES]

1247
01:02:02,469 --> 01:02:04,972
[ENTHRALLING
INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

1248
01:02:06,682 --> 01:02:08,017
[YELLS]

1249
01:02:08,475 --> 01:02:09,602
[GASPS]

1250
01:02:09,685 --> 01:02:10,853
Otto!

1251
01:02:12,229 --> 01:02:13,522
[TYRES SCREECH]

1252
01:02:13,606 --> 01:02:16,942
You do not want to try me
today, mister.

1253
01:02:17,026 --> 01:02:19,445
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1254
01:02:19,528 --> 01:02:20,946
[ROARING]

1255
01:02:25,117 --> 01:02:26,577
[OTTO YELLING]

1256
01:02:28,621 --> 01:02:30,039
Get him!

1257
01:02:30,122 --> 01:02:31,916
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

1258
01:02:38,923 --> 01:02:39,965
[TYRES SCREECH]

1259
01:02:41,967 --> 01:02:42,927
[PANTING]

1260
01:02:44,219 --> 01:02:45,054
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1261
01:02:47,556 --> 01:02:50,059
[ENTHRALLING
INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

1262
01:02:56,941 --> 01:02:59,234
[ALARM BUZZING]

1263
01:03:00,277 --> 01:03:01,987
- [YELLING]
- [TYRES SCREECHING]

1264
01:03:07,868 --> 01:03:08,869
Phew!

1265
01:03:08,953 --> 01:03:13,791
Welcome back... Victor.

1266
01:03:18,128 --> 01:03:19,546
Hey, Jinx.

1267
01:03:20,005 --> 01:03:22,800
Why are you here?
I... I was bringing this to you.

1268
01:03:22,883 --> 01:03:25,928
Were you? Really?

1269
01:03:26,011 --> 01:03:28,889
Yeah, of course I was.
That's what we agreed to, right?

1270
01:03:28,973 --> 01:03:29,974
Mmm.

1271
01:03:31,475 --> 01:03:32,726
[VIC SIGHS]

1272
01:03:32,810 --> 01:03:37,731
- So, you and me square now?
- [CHUCKLES] Not quite.

1273
01:03:37,815 --> 01:03:40,401
There's still the matter
of those five years

1274
01:03:40,484 --> 01:03:41,777
I lost because of you.

1275
01:03:41,860 --> 01:03:44,571
What?
But I thought this settled that.

1276
01:03:44,655 --> 01:03:46,907
[LAUGHING]

1277
01:03:46,991 --> 01:03:50,786
It was never about the milk.
It was about you getting caught

1278
01:03:50,869 --> 01:03:54,039
trying to steal it
and being sent to the pound

1279
01:03:54,123 --> 01:03:55,958
like I was.

1280
01:03:56,750 --> 01:04:00,129
You see, Vic,
I needed you to suffer

1281
01:04:00,212 --> 01:04:03,549
like I did.

1282
01:04:03,632 --> 01:04:04,800
Oh.

1283
01:04:05,426 --> 01:04:06,927
I see.

1284
01:04:07,011 --> 01:04:08,554
And I'm guessing
you have an idea

1285
01:04:08,637 --> 01:04:10,514
about how that should happen.

1286
01:04:11,015 --> 01:04:14,393
As a matter of fact, I do.

1287
01:04:21,483 --> 01:04:23,318
I can't believe he did that.

1288
01:04:24,069 --> 01:04:29,241
He ran out, and he left me.
Again.

1289
01:04:30,451 --> 01:04:31,994
I thought he'd changed,
but it was...

1290
01:04:33,120 --> 01:04:34,371
it was a lie.

1291
01:04:35,330 --> 01:04:36,415
All of it.

1292
01:04:38,125 --> 01:04:40,294
- [MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING]
- [SIGHS]

1293
01:04:41,503 --> 01:04:43,422
How could I have been so stupid?

1294
01:04:45,215 --> 01:04:46,091
[SIGHS]

1295
01:04:48,594 --> 01:04:52,222
MAURICE: Oh, come on, kid.
Don't beat yourself up.

1296
01:04:53,098 --> 01:04:56,101
Vic, man,
we've all been burned by Vic.

1297
01:04:56,185 --> 01:04:58,562
ALL: Yeah, that's right.
Burned every cat I know.

1298
01:04:58,645 --> 01:04:59,980
[ALL CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

1299
01:05:00,105 --> 01:05:02,858
Oh, yeah, the one thing
about Vic you can count on

1300
01:05:02,941 --> 01:05:05,611
- is that you can't count on him.
- Tell me about it.

1301
01:05:05,694 --> 01:05:06,570
CAT: Yeah.

1302
01:05:06,653 --> 01:05:07,821
MAURICE: Yeah,
I'll tell you about it.

1303
01:05:07,905 --> 01:05:11,325
Long story short, we all used
to run in a pack

1304
01:05:11,408 --> 01:05:13,619
until we had to kick him
out the crew.

1305
01:05:13,702 --> 01:05:14,787
[CATS CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

1306
01:05:14,870 --> 01:05:17,414
Like I said,
couldn't count on him.

1307
01:05:17,498 --> 01:05:18,749
Sounds about right.

1308
01:05:18,832 --> 01:05:20,584
He'd leave
in the middle of a job

1309
01:05:20,667 --> 01:05:22,127
just to go see his kid.

1310
01:05:22,753 --> 01:05:25,547
Yeah, he said
he wanted to check up on him.

1311
01:05:25,631 --> 01:05:27,549
Make sure he was doing okay.

1312
01:05:27,633 --> 01:05:30,344
But get this,
he'd never actually visit.

1313
01:05:30,427 --> 01:05:31,887
He'd just sit across the street

1314
01:05:31,970 --> 01:05:34,264
from his kid's house
in a giant oak tree.

1315
01:05:34,348 --> 01:05:36,642
- That never happened.
- He'd watch that kid eat...

1316
01:05:36,725 --> 01:05:38,602
- and eat and eat...
- ALL: ...and eat...

1317
01:05:38,685 --> 01:05:41,563
- He put a notch in the bark...
- ...and eat, and eat, and eat.

1318
01:05:41,647 --> 01:05:44,149
- ...every time he was there.
- Yeah. Sure, he did.

1319
01:05:44,233 --> 01:05:47,820
He'd go every Sunday night,
rain or shine.

1320
01:05:47,903 --> 01:05:49,363
Said that it was his kid's...

1321
01:05:49,446 --> 01:05:52,032
ALL: ...family dinner night.

1322
01:05:52,116 --> 01:05:56,120
[CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

1323
01:05:57,079 --> 01:05:58,914
Okay, hate to tell you guys...

1324
01:05:59,957 --> 01:06:02,918
I guarantee
that never happened. Okay?

1325
01:06:03,001 --> 01:06:06,255
You all fell for another one of
Vic's lies. We all have.

1326
01:06:07,089 --> 01:06:09,049
Because that's
what he does best.

1327
01:06:10,008 --> 01:06:14,138
[ODIE BARKING]

1328
01:06:14,221 --> 01:06:16,181
Odie? Odie!
How did you get out?

1329
01:06:16,265 --> 01:06:18,100
Quick, pick the lock on my cage.

1330
01:06:18,183 --> 01:06:19,810
- Garfield, there you are!
- [GASPS]

1331
01:06:19,893 --> 01:06:22,437
Jon! Oh! Take me away
from all this.

1332
01:06:22,521 --> 01:06:24,648
You can't imagine
what I've been through.

1333
01:06:24,731 --> 01:06:26,650
- You want this one too?
- Oh, yes, I do.

1334
01:06:26,733 --> 01:06:27,943
- I was hung upside down.
- You sure he's yours?

1335
01:06:28,026 --> 01:06:29,403
He didn't have a tag.

1336
01:06:29,486 --> 01:06:31,238
- I jumped a train.
- Yeah. He has a tag.

1337
01:06:31,321 --> 01:06:35,117
Huh? I have a collar and a tag?
How long have I had those?

1338
01:06:35,200 --> 01:06:37,077
Okay. I'm just gonna
need you to hold.

1339
01:06:37,161 --> 01:06:39,788
I will not hold!
I am done holding!

1340
01:06:39,872 --> 01:06:43,584
The Jon who was on hold is dead.
Do you understand?

1341
01:06:43,667 --> 01:06:45,294
[UPBEAT ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

1342
01:06:45,377 --> 01:06:48,505
That's right. I'm back, baby!

1343
01:06:51,008 --> 01:06:53,343
I was just talking about you,
wasn't I?

1344
01:06:56,180 --> 01:06:57,931
Oh! I've missed you too.

1345
01:06:59,892 --> 01:07:02,311
WOMAN ON TV:
<i>Coochie coochie coo!</i>

1346
01:07:06,899 --> 01:07:08,400
Pooky!

1347
01:07:11,153 --> 01:07:13,655
I have a lot to tell you.
You're never gonna believe it.

1348
01:07:14,489 --> 01:07:17,034
Crazy stuff happened.
I slept outside, twice!

1349
01:07:17,117 --> 01:07:18,243
I know. Me.

1350
01:07:18,327 --> 01:07:20,746
Oh! And I got you
this commemorative pin.

1351
01:07:21,622 --> 01:07:23,165
- JON: Dinner time!
- [GASPS]

1352
01:07:23,248 --> 01:07:24,249
Talk later.

1353
01:07:24,374 --> 01:07:27,461
[UPBEAT MUSIC CONTINUES]

1354
01:07:40,515 --> 01:07:42,059
Ah!

1355
01:07:42,142 --> 01:07:43,518
JON: Say when.

1356
01:07:43,602 --> 01:07:46,230
Never, Jon.
Bury me in cheese.

1357
01:07:48,941 --> 01:07:50,400
JON: I have two more
in the freezer.

1358
01:07:50,484 --> 01:07:52,653
- Let me know when you want 'em.
- [BELL DINGS]

1359
01:07:52,736 --> 01:07:54,613
I'm gonna go check on dessert.

1360
01:07:54,696 --> 01:07:56,698
Oh, I apologise in advance.

1361
01:07:56,782 --> 01:07:59,284
The eating you're about to see
will not be pretty

1362
01:07:59,368 --> 01:08:00,786
and if you have
young children,

1363
01:08:00,869 --> 01:08:02,829
this would be a good time
for them to leave the room.

1364
01:08:02,913 --> 01:08:03,914
Mmm-hmm!

1365
01:08:10,295 --> 01:08:14,049
[SLOW INSTRUMENTAL
MUSIC PLAYING]

1366
01:08:15,884 --> 01:08:18,595
CAT: <i>He yd just sit across
the street from his kid's house</i>

1367
01:08:18,679 --> 01:08:20,138
<i>in a giant oak tree.</i>

1368
01:08:39,449 --> 01:08:41,576
[STOMACH RUMBLING]

1369
01:08:41,660 --> 01:08:44,329
I know, I know.
We're coming back.

1370
01:08:45,664 --> 01:08:47,582
I just need to check
something out first.

1371
01:08:48,250 --> 01:08:52,087
[SLOW INSTRUMENTAL
MUSIC CONTINUES]

1372
01:09:00,762 --> 01:09:02,306
[TYRES SCREECHING]

1373
01:09:08,895 --> 01:09:11,106
CAT: <i>He put a notch
in the bark...</i>

1374
01:09:12,316 --> 01:09:13,942
<i>every time he was there.</i>

1375
01:09:17,487 --> 01:09:18,488
[GRUNTS]

1376
01:09:20,532 --> 01:09:22,284
[STRAINING]

1377
01:09:31,126 --> 01:09:32,919
"He left a notch."

1378
01:09:34,046 --> 01:09:35,422
[SIGHS]

1379
01:09:35,505 --> 01:09:36,673
Yeah, right.

1380
01:09:45,724 --> 01:09:48,060
[UPLIFTING MUSIC PLAYING]

1381
01:10:19,049 --> 01:10:20,092
He was here.

1382
01:10:21,218 --> 01:10:22,344
He saw me grow up.

1383
01:10:22,928 --> 01:10:24,262
[ODIE BARKS]

1384
01:10:25,806 --> 01:10:26,848
Oh! Ow!

1385
01:10:26,932 --> 01:10:28,141
Wow, that really stings.

1386
01:10:28,225 --> 01:10:30,268
I don't know
why I didn't think it would.

1387
01:10:30,352 --> 01:10:31,603
Give me a second.

1388
01:10:31,686 --> 01:10:33,313
[PANTS]

1389
01:10:33,563 --> 01:10:34,648
Vic loves us!

1390
01:10:34,731 --> 01:10:37,067
Me first, of course,
but then you too!

1391
01:10:37,150 --> 01:10:39,236
But me, a lot, and first!

1392
01:10:39,319 --> 01:10:40,487
[SCOFFS]

1393
01:10:40,612 --> 01:10:43,073
Wait, but if he loves me, us,

1394
01:10:43,156 --> 01:10:46,243
why would he let me, us,
get captured at the dairy?

1395
01:10:46,326 --> 01:10:48,453
Unless... [GASPS] He wanted

1396
01:10:48,537 --> 01:10:50,080
- us to get captured!
- WOMAN: Hey!

1397
01:10:50,163 --> 01:10:51,164
- Yes!
- Hey, watch it!

1398
01:10:51,248 --> 01:10:53,667
He knew that Jinx wasn't gonna
let him off the hook.

1399
01:10:53,750 --> 01:10:54,751
But if we got caught,

1400
01:10:54,835 --> 01:10:56,711
- we'd get sent to the pound...
- [HONKS]

1401
01:10:56,795 --> 01:10:58,213
...and Jon would come to get us!

1402
01:10:58,296 --> 01:10:59,423
Don't you see, Odie?

1403
01:10:59,506 --> 01:11:02,050
- He was trying to save us!
- MAN: Losers!

1404
01:11:03,718 --> 01:11:05,387
We have to go save my dad.

1405
01:11:06,096 --> 01:11:09,141
And here's
your favourite dessert,

1406
01:11:09,224 --> 01:11:11,810
Mount Candy-toa!

1407
01:11:11,935 --> 01:11:13,895
Uh, guys?

1408
01:11:13,979 --> 01:11:16,148
[RUMBLING]

1409
01:11:16,231 --> 01:11:18,191
- [EXPLODING]
- [GRUNTS]

1410
01:11:18,358 --> 01:11:20,527
Oh! Come on!

1411
01:11:22,237 --> 01:11:26,366
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

1412
01:11:29,035 --> 01:11:31,288
What is this?

1413
01:11:34,708 --> 01:11:35,834
[BOTH GASPING]

1414
01:11:37,419 --> 01:11:38,795
[BOTH GASPING]

1415
01:11:45,260 --> 01:11:47,929
[GASPS] Half a star
for Mamma Leoni's?

1416
01:11:48,013 --> 01:11:50,432
[GROWLS] She's a monster.

1417
01:11:51,016 --> 01:11:51,933
[YIPS]

1418
01:11:52,976 --> 01:11:54,186
She's gonna tie him up...

1419
01:11:54,436 --> 01:11:55,770
take him on a train...

1420
01:11:55,854 --> 01:11:57,105
- [JINX CACKLING]
- [GASPS]

1421
01:11:57,189 --> 01:11:59,649
She's going to throw him off
the Mile High Bridge!

1422
01:11:59,733 --> 01:12:01,985
We're gonna need help.
Who can we call?

1423
01:12:02,861 --> 01:12:03,945
Hmm!

1424
01:12:04,029 --> 01:12:05,322
- Ah!
- [GASPS]

1425
01:12:05,405 --> 01:12:07,449
Ugh! You've got
a lot of waxy build-up.

1426
01:12:07,532 --> 01:12:08,742
What's your Q-tip routine?

1427
01:12:08,825 --> 01:12:10,702
- [GROANS]
- You're right, you're right.

1428
01:12:10,785 --> 01:12:12,787
We can deal
with that situation later.

1429
01:12:12,871 --> 01:12:15,665
Hello? Hello?
Is anyone there? Hello?

1430
01:12:17,918 --> 01:12:19,127
[GROANS]

1431
01:12:19,211 --> 01:12:20,587
OTTO: <i>Get off the line.</i>

1432
01:12:20,670 --> 01:12:22,547
<i>This acorn
is for emergency use only.</i>

1433
01:12:22,631 --> 01:12:25,467
Otto! Otto, please, listen.

1434
01:12:25,592 --> 01:12:27,677
I wanna make good
on our original deal,

1435
01:12:27,761 --> 01:12:30,680
but...
but I need a favour first.

1436
01:12:34,809 --> 01:12:36,061
Otto, are you still there

1437
01:12:36,144 --> 01:12:37,812
or are you taking
a dramatic pause?

1438
01:12:40,899 --> 01:12:41,900
<i>I'm listening.</i>

1439
01:12:41,983 --> 01:12:43,652
[TRAIN HORN BLARING]

1440
01:12:46,196 --> 01:12:47,447
Hmm.

1441
01:12:47,531 --> 01:12:48,949
You know, Vic,

1442
01:12:49,032 --> 01:12:52,619
you only have yourself to blame
for this.

1443
01:12:52,702 --> 01:12:54,204
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

1444
01:12:54,329 --> 01:12:56,456
Right. Look,

1445
01:12:56,540 --> 01:12:59,125
there's got to be some way
for me to make this right.

1446
01:12:59,209 --> 01:13:01,253
I mean, I know
we can think of somethin'.

1447
01:13:01,336 --> 01:13:04,965
Oh, there is, and you will.

1448
01:13:05,048 --> 01:13:06,925
[MUSIC INCREASES IN TEMPO]

1449
01:13:07,008 --> 01:13:07,968
[THUNDERCLAP]

1450
01:13:08,426 --> 01:13:10,095
[HORN BLARING]

1451
01:13:11,555 --> 01:13:14,975
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1452
01:13:18,228 --> 01:13:19,396
So, once I get on the train...

1453
01:13:19,479 --> 01:13:20,981
I untie Vic and we jump off

1454
01:13:21,064 --> 01:13:22,524
right as
the train gets to the bridge.

1455
01:13:22,607 --> 01:13:24,651
Correct. Chipmunk
will be waiting for you.

1456
01:13:26,653 --> 01:13:28,697
[OVER RADIO]
<i>Confirm your status, Chipmunk.</i>

1457
01:13:28,780 --> 01:13:29,948
[BARKS]

1458
01:13:30,031 --> 01:13:32,242
If you don't jump right as
the train gets to the bridge,

1459
01:13:32,325 --> 01:13:33,577
you'll miss the net.

1460
01:13:34,327 --> 01:13:36,580
Got it. It's getting close.

1461
01:13:36,663 --> 01:13:38,748
Have you considered
throwing a rope over a branch

1462
01:13:38,832 --> 01:13:40,792
and just swinging
onto the passing train instead?

1463
01:13:40,875 --> 01:13:41,876
You watch too much TV.

1464
01:13:41,960 --> 01:13:43,003
I've never watched TV.

1465
01:13:43,086 --> 01:13:45,380
Well, this way is much better
than your rope idea.

1466
01:13:45,463 --> 01:13:46,965
Better than the versatile,
reliable rope?

1467
01:13:47,048 --> 01:13:49,259
Look, I've studied the science.
I know what I'm doing.

1468
01:13:49,342 --> 01:13:51,678
And you think you can battle
these villains on your own?

1469
01:13:51,761 --> 01:13:54,556
Oh yeah. I have a plan. Odie?

1470
01:13:55,098 --> 01:13:56,099
<i>Make the order.</i>

1471
01:13:56,182 --> 01:13:57,058
[YIPS]

1472
01:13:57,809 --> 01:13:59,019
[BEEPS]

1473
01:13:59,102 --> 01:14:00,729
Now get ready to fling me

1474
01:14:00,812 --> 01:14:02,856
in the direction
of that moving train.

1475
01:14:02,939 --> 01:14:03,982
[GRUNTS]

1476
01:14:08,612 --> 01:14:10,822
- Get ready.
- [HORN BLARING]

1477
01:14:11,698 --> 01:14:13,575
If I don't make it back...

1478
01:14:14,200 --> 01:14:16,286
tell my story. Now!

1479
01:14:18,288 --> 01:14:20,040
Roadkill! You're too high!
You're gonna miss it!

1480
01:14:20,123 --> 01:14:21,833
No, no, this is how you do it!

1481
01:14:21,916 --> 01:14:23,376
It's called
the ricochet approach!

1482
01:14:26,379 --> 01:14:28,423
Ooh! [LAUGHS WICKEDLY]

1483
01:14:28,506 --> 01:14:29,799
It won't be long now.

1484
01:14:29,924 --> 01:14:32,093
I can't tell you
how excited I am

1485
01:14:32,177 --> 01:14:33,720
for what's about to happen next.

1486
01:14:34,304 --> 01:14:36,056
[GRUNTING]

1487
01:14:36,139 --> 01:14:38,558
Dad! I'm here to rescue you!

1488
01:14:38,642 --> 01:14:39,643
No, no, no, Junior!

1489
01:14:39,726 --> 01:14:41,061
- Get outta here!
- I'm gonna untie you,

1490
01:14:41,144 --> 01:14:42,228
and we're gonna
jump off the train!

1491
01:14:42,312 --> 01:14:44,022
- No! Just leave me and go!
- I didn't come this far...

1492
01:14:44,105 --> 01:14:45,815
just to turn around,
let me untie you!

1493
01:14:45,899 --> 01:14:47,942
- You're ruining everything!
- [GASPS]

1494
01:14:49,110 --> 01:14:50,111
Quick, this way!

1495
01:14:51,237 --> 01:14:54,115
[JINX YELLING]

1496
01:14:59,204 --> 01:15:01,956
Oh, you half-wit! Get them!

1497
01:15:02,916 --> 01:15:05,919
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1498
01:15:10,465 --> 01:15:11,925
[SNARLS]

1499
01:15:12,133 --> 01:15:14,719
[GRUNTING]

1500
01:15:16,096 --> 01:15:17,305
[STRAINING]

1501
01:15:18,682 --> 01:15:20,975
[GRUNTING]

1502
01:15:24,104 --> 01:15:25,563
[BOTH GASPING]

1503
01:15:31,861 --> 01:15:33,488
The bridge is comin' up!

1504
01:15:33,571 --> 01:15:34,989
We gotta get to the caboose now!

1505
01:15:35,073 --> 01:15:36,991
- What? Why?
- Just follow my lead!

1506
01:15:38,493 --> 01:15:39,494
Wow!

1507
01:15:42,706 --> 01:15:44,916
- Ha! [LAUGHS]
- [BOTH GASP]

1508
01:15:47,001 --> 01:15:48,420
Oi, kitty cat!

1509
01:15:48,503 --> 01:15:51,506
Did you expect
to take us on all by yourself?

1510
01:15:51,589 --> 01:15:54,884
No. I brought... takeout.

1511
01:15:54,968 --> 01:15:56,469
- [DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]
- Huh?

1512
01:15:56,761 --> 01:15:57,929
Huh?

1513
01:16:04,853 --> 01:16:08,273
[HEROIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1514
01:16:14,612 --> 01:16:15,447
[GRUNTS]

1515
01:16:20,577 --> 01:16:22,162
[GRUNTS]

1516
01:16:26,583 --> 01:16:28,752
[GRUNTING]

1517
01:16:32,338 --> 01:16:33,173
[HISSES]

1518
01:16:40,180 --> 01:16:41,264
Ah-ha!

1519
01:16:41,890 --> 01:16:42,932
[GRUNTS]

1520
01:16:43,016 --> 01:16:45,143
I never understood
the purpose of salad

1521
01:16:45,226 --> 01:16:47,061
until this exact moment!

1522
01:16:47,145 --> 01:16:49,397
[GRUNTING]

1523
01:16:49,981 --> 01:16:51,983
- [DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]
- [GASPS]

1524
01:16:54,652 --> 01:16:56,654
Go, go! Now!

1525
01:16:56,738 --> 01:16:57,864
Get after him!

1526
01:16:57,947 --> 01:16:59,699
[SNARLS]

1527
01:17:01,659 --> 01:17:02,494
[YELLS]

1528
01:17:03,036 --> 01:17:05,121
[GRUNTING]

1529
01:17:07,040 --> 01:17:08,208
[GROANS] Huh?

1530
01:17:10,335 --> 01:17:11,419
[CHUCKLES]

1531
01:17:14,839 --> 01:17:15,882
Ow!

1532
01:17:19,552 --> 01:17:21,054
Yeah, in case
you were wonderin',

1533
01:17:21,137 --> 01:17:22,680
I do my own stunts.

1534
01:17:22,764 --> 01:17:23,765
Me...

1535
01:17:24,891 --> 01:17:26,100
and Tom Cruise.

1536
01:17:26,184 --> 01:17:27,936
[SNARLING]

1537
01:17:29,813 --> 01:17:31,481
Junior!

1538
01:17:31,564 --> 01:17:33,817
[GRUNTING]

1539
01:17:36,694 --> 01:17:37,821
[LAUGHS]

1540
01:17:37,904 --> 01:17:38,905
JINX: Stop him!

1541
01:17:38,988 --> 01:17:40,448
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1542
01:17:56,005 --> 01:17:57,257
[GASPING]

1543
01:17:59,425 --> 01:18:00,760
Now <i>that's</i> amazing!

1544
01:18:00,844 --> 01:18:02,136
I can't feel my tongue.

1545
01:18:02,220 --> 01:18:03,221
OTTO: <i>Roadkill!</i>

1546
01:18:03,304 --> 01:18:05,139
<i>Are you at the caboose,
ready to jump?</i>

1547
01:18:06,850 --> 01:18:07,892
[GASPS]

1548
01:18:11,187 --> 01:18:14,941
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1549
01:18:27,871 --> 01:18:29,247
Dad! Dad!

1550
01:18:29,330 --> 01:18:31,165
Jump, Junior! I'll catch you!

1551
01:18:31,249 --> 01:18:34,168
[YELLING]

1552
01:18:37,964 --> 01:18:39,257
[GRUNTS]

1553
01:18:40,341 --> 01:18:41,384
[GROWLING]

1554
01:18:44,721 --> 01:18:46,014
[BOTH GASP]

1555
01:18:49,684 --> 01:18:51,644
[HORN BLARING]

1556
01:18:54,063 --> 01:18:54,898
[GASPS]

1557
01:18:57,025 --> 01:18:58,401
What do we do now?

1558
01:18:58,484 --> 01:18:59,652
We do this!

1559
01:18:59,736 --> 01:19:01,696
[YELLING]

1560
01:19:01,863 --> 01:19:02,822
[GASPS]

1561
01:19:03,698 --> 01:19:04,699
See ya, everyone.

1562
01:19:09,787 --> 01:19:12,290
The net's too tight!

1563
01:19:12,373 --> 01:19:13,791
Roadkill, the net is too tight!

1564
01:19:13,875 --> 01:19:14,876
I heard!

1565
01:19:15,209 --> 01:19:16,669
- [SHRIEKS]
- [YELLING]

1566
01:19:21,799 --> 01:19:23,885
Hello again, welcome back!

1567
01:19:24,218 --> 01:19:25,803
Now, where were we?

1568
01:19:31,851 --> 01:19:33,061
[VIC GRUNTS]

1569
01:19:35,229 --> 01:19:36,648
No, no!
Don't throw them over just yet.

1570
01:19:36,731 --> 01:19:38,107
- No!
- [STRAINING]

1571
01:19:38,191 --> 01:19:40,151
I want to find the perfect place

1572
01:19:40,234 --> 01:19:42,654
for them
to make the biggest splat.

1573
01:19:43,321 --> 01:19:45,615
Hey, hey! Junior!
Junior, Junior.

1574
01:19:45,698 --> 01:19:47,867
Get ready! Almost there!

1575
01:19:49,035 --> 01:19:51,120
I'm sorry
my rescue didn't work out.

1576
01:19:51,245 --> 01:19:54,749
- No, you gave me another chance.
- [SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

1577
01:19:54,832 --> 01:19:56,417
That's all that matters.

1578
01:20:00,546 --> 01:20:03,216
Now, now! Drop them now!

1579
01:20:03,299 --> 01:20:04,175
Huh?

1580
01:20:04,926 --> 01:20:06,469
What are you waiting for?

1581
01:20:09,347 --> 01:20:11,432
Their love for one another
indicates that

1582
01:20:11,516 --> 01:20:13,559
despite their
current circumstance,

1583
01:20:13,643 --> 01:20:15,353
they are at peace.

1584
01:20:15,436 --> 01:20:18,564
- Because they are together.
- So?

1585
01:20:18,648 --> 01:20:21,150
If the point of your revenge
was to hurt them,

1586
01:20:21,234 --> 01:20:23,444
it has done the opposite.

1587
01:20:23,569 --> 01:20:25,279
It's actually textbook irony!

1588
01:20:25,363 --> 01:20:28,491
And we're no longer
comfortable with your plan.

1589
01:20:28,574 --> 01:20:29,534
[GRUNTS]

1590
01:20:29,617 --> 01:20:31,953
You two
are still as weak as you were

1591
01:20:32,036 --> 01:20:34,455
when I found you
snivelling in the pound.

1592
01:20:34,539 --> 01:20:36,708
"Ooh, no one will adopt us.

1593
01:20:36,791 --> 01:20:38,793
"I never grew into my folds.

1594
01:20:38,876 --> 01:20:41,212
"I hide behind them
because I'm socially awkward.

1595
01:20:41,295 --> 01:20:42,672
"Please, somebody love me

1596
01:20:42,797 --> 01:20:44,674
"even though I can't sit still
for more than ten seconds

1597
01:20:44,757 --> 01:20:46,968
and have the attention span
of a bloody goldfish!"

1598
01:20:47,510 --> 01:20:50,430
We did everything
you ever asked of us.

1599
01:20:50,513 --> 01:20:52,598
I even spoke
with this ridiculous accent

1600
01:20:52,682 --> 01:20:54,434
to make you feel more at home.

1601
01:20:54,517 --> 01:20:55,727
But no more!

1602
01:20:55,810 --> 01:20:58,021
[NEW YORK ACCENT]
I'm New York, loud and proud!

1603
01:20:58,104 --> 01:21:00,314
I love myself the way I am

1604
01:21:00,398 --> 01:21:03,192
and I'm a big, brave, boy, baby!

1605
01:21:03,317 --> 01:21:05,987
And I've been
working on my attention span.

1606
01:21:06,070 --> 01:21:07,697
[GASPS] Is that
a hot-air balloon?

1607
01:21:07,780 --> 01:21:09,991
[GROANS] You two...

1608
01:21:10,408 --> 01:21:11,701
are...

1609
01:21:11,784 --> 01:21:13,036
Worthless!

1610
01:21:14,454 --> 01:21:17,623
[YELLING]

1611
01:21:17,707 --> 01:21:19,917
[LAUGHS MANIACALLY]

1612
01:21:20,418 --> 01:21:22,920
[GRUNTS AND SCREAMS]

1613
01:21:23,379 --> 01:21:27,300
[ALL YELLING]

1614
01:21:36,267 --> 01:21:39,729
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1615
01:21:43,858 --> 01:21:45,985
- [GRUNTS]
- [GASPS]

1616
01:21:50,156 --> 01:21:52,575
[ALL GASPING]

1617
01:21:52,658 --> 01:21:56,370
Might I just say as someone else
with a zaftig figure,

1618
01:21:56,454 --> 01:21:58,039
you have a beautiful body, sir.

1619
01:21:58,372 --> 01:21:59,582
[ALL GASP]

1620
01:21:59,749 --> 01:22:00,792
Oh, dear!

1621
01:22:00,875 --> 01:22:02,835
[ALL YELLING]

1622
01:22:04,754 --> 01:22:07,757
Rope. Versatile. Reliable.

1623
01:22:07,882 --> 01:22:09,342
There's something
about your cadence

1624
01:22:09,425 --> 01:22:10,843
that really throws me,
but thank you.

1625
01:22:11,302 --> 01:22:14,013
[JINX YELLING]

1626
01:22:14,472 --> 01:22:15,348
[JINX MIAOWS]

1627
01:22:17,475 --> 01:22:18,601
[GRUNTS]

1628
01:22:18,810 --> 01:22:20,478
[STRAINING]

1629
01:22:20,645 --> 01:22:22,855
[LAUGHING]

1630
01:22:23,106 --> 01:22:24,107
Tee-hee!

1631
01:22:26,192 --> 01:22:29,195
Tossing me off the train?
Did not see that coming.

1632
01:22:29,278 --> 01:22:30,780
Well, when you live in the wild,

1633
01:22:30,863 --> 01:22:32,907
you gotta keep your head
on a swivel.

1634
01:22:32,990 --> 01:22:34,492
Right.

1635
01:22:35,201 --> 01:22:38,412
It's basic Outdoor Cat 101.

1636
01:22:38,496 --> 01:22:40,498
And that had bird poop on it.

1637
01:22:40,998 --> 01:22:43,000
Hey. You good, Roadkill?

1638
01:22:44,710 --> 01:22:45,795
Not quite.

1639
01:22:45,878 --> 01:22:48,631
There's one last thing
to take care of.

1640
01:22:48,881 --> 01:22:49,882
Cut to...

1641
01:22:51,092 --> 01:22:52,718
[TYPEWRITER CLACKING]

1642
01:22:57,598 --> 01:23:00,351
GARFIELD: <i>It was
a dark and foggy night.</i>

1643
01:23:00,434 --> 01:23:05,064
<i>The air was damp
and heavier than a broken heart.</i>

1644
01:23:05,148 --> 01:23:07,150
<i>On nights like this,
you can't swing a cat</i>

1645
01:23:07,233 --> 01:23:09,527
<i>without hittin' shady characters</i>

1646
01:23:09,610 --> 01:23:12,655
<i>makin' shady deals
all over town.</i>

1647
01:23:15,366 --> 01:23:18,828
<i>Oh, but this night
was going to be... different.</i>

1648
01:23:18,953 --> 01:23:21,455
<i>Justice was about to be served.</i>

1649
01:23:21,539 --> 01:23:26,043
<i>With a helping
of retribution on the side.</i>

1650
01:23:26,127 --> 01:23:28,713
Is that... [CLEARS THROAT]
the package?

1651
01:23:28,796 --> 01:23:30,715
[ELECTRONICALLY ALTERED VOICE]
<i>It is.</i>

1652
01:23:30,798 --> 01:23:32,133
Then we have a deal.

1653
01:23:32,216 --> 01:23:33,509
[WHISTLES]

1654
01:23:37,263 --> 01:23:39,182
<i>No one will come
looking for her?</i>

1655
01:23:39,265 --> 01:23:41,475
Nope. I did what you said.

1656
01:23:41,559 --> 01:23:43,186
I burned her paperwork.

1657
01:23:43,269 --> 01:23:45,605
And then shredded it
and burned it some more.

1658
01:23:45,688 --> 01:23:48,357
It's like she never existed.

1659
01:23:48,774 --> 01:23:51,736
Except for the image of her face
on millions of dairy products.

1660
01:23:53,279 --> 01:23:54,822
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

1661
01:23:54,906 --> 01:23:56,115
[BELL DINGING]

1662
01:24:11,047 --> 01:24:12,340
[IN NORMAL VOICE] This...

1663
01:24:12,423 --> 01:24:13,799
[RASPY VOICE]
<i>never happened.</i>

1664
01:24:14,300 --> 01:24:15,301
Agreed.

1665
01:24:17,053 --> 01:24:20,389
- [GROWLS]
- Oh, save it, Cat Fancy.

1666
01:24:20,473 --> 01:24:22,016
I know you planned
the milk truck heist...

1667
01:24:22,099 --> 01:24:24,060
and then tried to throw those
innocent cats off a train

1668
01:24:24,143 --> 01:24:25,144
to cover it up.

1669
01:24:25,228 --> 01:24:27,146
The boys told me everything.

1670
01:24:27,230 --> 01:24:28,314
[GASPS]

1671
01:24:30,066 --> 01:24:31,150
Mmm-mmm-mmm.

1672
01:24:31,943 --> 01:24:33,527
[GROWLS]

1673
01:24:38,574 --> 01:24:39,951
Oh! [GASPS]

1674
01:24:43,621 --> 01:24:45,206
Otto! Oh!

1675
01:24:46,123 --> 01:24:48,834
[SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

1676
01:24:51,045 --> 01:24:52,755
You are my day.

1677
01:24:53,339 --> 01:24:55,549
You are my night.

1678
01:24:57,718 --> 01:25:01,389
["LET'S GET IT ON" PLAYING]

1679
01:25:13,526 --> 01:25:14,902
[MOOING]

1680
01:25:22,368 --> 01:25:25,955
[SLOW INSTRUMENTAL
MUSIC PLAYING]

1681
01:25:31,794 --> 01:25:33,296
Uh...

1682
01:25:33,629 --> 01:25:36,382
[SIGHS] Well, this is us.

1683
01:25:37,049 --> 01:25:39,093
Right. You're home.

1684
01:25:42,096 --> 01:25:44,265
- Hey, listen, I'm sorry.
- I just want to say I'm sorry.

1685
01:25:45,182 --> 01:25:46,767
What are you sorry for?

1686
01:25:50,187 --> 01:25:51,564
For misjudging you.

1687
01:25:52,023 --> 01:25:53,024
Oh.

1688
01:25:53,607 --> 01:25:55,985
Well. Thanks.

1689
01:25:56,694 --> 01:25:58,654
Well, I just wanted to
apologise to you for...

1690
01:25:58,738 --> 01:26:01,991
Everything bad that happened
to us the last three days?

1691
01:26:02,074 --> 01:26:03,868
You know, you had your hand in

1692
01:26:03,951 --> 01:26:06,037
a few bad decisions
back there too, but...

1693
01:26:07,121 --> 01:26:08,205
[SIGHS]

1694
01:26:08,289 --> 01:26:10,791
Yeah, I'm sorry for
dragging you into my world.

1695
01:26:11,334 --> 01:26:13,377
This is where you belong,

1696
01:26:13,461 --> 01:26:15,504
here with Jon and...

1697
01:26:15,588 --> 01:26:17,465
What's your name again? Odor?

1698
01:26:17,548 --> 01:26:19,592
Huh? [SNARLS]

1699
01:26:20,217 --> 01:26:21,427
[YIPS]

1700
01:26:22,345 --> 01:26:25,514
- So... uh, yeah, I should go.
- Yeah, yeah.

1701
01:26:25,639 --> 01:26:27,266
I mean, unless...
you'd want to come in?

1702
01:26:27,350 --> 01:26:28,934
Nah. No, no.
I don't think that would work.

1703
01:26:29,018 --> 01:26:31,812
- You know, I'm an outdoor cat.
- Right. Sure. Sure.

